{{Infobox ethnic group | group = Chechens in France | image = | population = '''30,000'''<ref>http://www.refworld.org/country,,,,AUT,,5139cf902,0.html</ref> | popplace = [[Paris]], [[Île-de-France]], [[Nice]], [[Strasbourg]] | langs = [[French language|French]], [[Chechen language|Chechen]], [[Russian language|Russian]] | rels = [[Sunni Islam]]
}} '''Chechens in France''' is a small diaspora in [[France]] but one of the most important groups in the [[Chechen people|Chechen diaspora]].
== History == The Chechen immigrants came in [[France]] at the early [[2000s (decade)|2000s]], because of the two [[Chechen Wars (disambiguation)|Chechen Wars]]. They came as [[political refugees]].<ref>http://www.refworld.org/country,,,,AUT,,5139cf902,0.html</ref> Today, there are approximately 30,000 [[Chechens]] in [[France]], and 60,000 in the [[European Union]].
